$ /dev/disk

Directories found under `/dev/disk` include:
  • `by-diskseq/`
  • `by-id/`
  • `by-label/`
  • `by-partlabel/`
  • `by-partuuid/`
  • `by-path/`
  • `by-uuid/`

? The «files» in these directories (at least in `by-diskseq`, `by-id`, `by-partuuid`, `by-path` and `by-uuid`) are symbolic links that point to the «real» devices or partitions.

sa:

  The `-j` flag of `→ Linux/shell/commands/iostat`.

  `→ Linux/fhs/dev`
